    <h2>PROJECTS</h2>
    <div class="project-entry">
      <h3>Password-Based Circuit Breaker</h3>
      <p>April-2025</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Developed a system where the circuit breaker can be operated securely through a user-entered password, preventing unauthorized access or tampering.</li>
        <li>Used the 8051 microcontroller to control the relay mechanism, which turns the power ON/OFF based on correct or incorrect password inputs.</li>
        <li>Implemented a basic keypad interface for password entry and a display (e.g., LCD) to provide feedback to the user (e.g., "Access Granted"/"Wrong Password").</li>
        <li>Technologies Used: Embedded C, 8051 Microcontroller, Relay Module, Keypad, LCD Display.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="project-entry">
      <h3>Facial Expression Based Driver Behaviour Monitoring System</h3>
      <p>MAY-2025</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Designed a real-time system to monitor driver alertness and emotions (like drowsiness, anger, distraction) using facial expression recognition.</li>
        <li>Used a camera module to capture the driver’s face and analyzed it using deep learning models (CNN) to classify expressions from real-time video frames.</li>
        <li>Implemented logic to trigger alerts or interventions (like audio beeps) when risky emotional states were detected for prolonged periods.</li>
        <li>Technologies Used: Python, OpenCV, Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
